 The APC National Caretaker Extraordinary/Convention Planning Committee has concluded arrangements for the commencement of membership registration and revalidation from Saturday, December 12, 2020, to Saturday, January 9, 2021. The Chairman of APC Caretaker Extraordinary/Convention Planning Committee and Governor of Yobe State, Mai-Mala Buni in a statement on Monday in Abuja said the exercise followed consultation with stakeholders, including President Muhammadu Buhari. Read Also: APC Governors, NEC, State Chairmen back tenure extension for Buni Caretaker Committee Buni urged all party members to revalidate their membership in their wards while prospective members are to take advantage of the membership registration process to join the ruling party. “The membership registration and revalidation will take place simultaneously in every Ward in the country. The process of distributing the membership registration and revalidation materials to all the States, Local Governments, and Wards will be concluded before December 12, 2020. “We, therefore, appeal to our States, Local Governments, and Wards leaders to take all the necessary steps to ensure smooth and transparent registration exercise. We will continue to provide updates of the process on regular basis”, he said.